          <span>Are expedition jackets provided? If not, what sort of jacket/wet weather gear should I pack?</span>
        </div>
        <div class="content">
          <p>
            Increasingly, our expedition operators are providing expedition jackets as part of their voyage inclusions. You will need to check, your voyage inclusions/exclusions for exact details.
          </p>
          <p>
            If your voyage does not include an expedition jacket, you will need to provide your own. In our Polar regions layered is what is most important, rather than the size of your jacket. By having quality socks and thermals and then applying simply layering techniques on top of these and quality waterproof outterwear, you will be well equipped.
          </p>
